OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774026671
OL,3,CDog owners warned to keep pets away
OL,4,Cfrom daffodils, tulips and bluebells
OL,6,F"However, while flowers such as
OL,7,Fdaffodils and tulips are great to look
OL,8,Fat, they can be problematic for our
OL,9,Fcanine friends, especially those who
OL,10,Flove to dig in the garden.
OL,12,F"Although cases of poisoning are rare,
OL,13,Fknowing which plants are dangerous and
OL,14,Fkeeping them out of reach can help
OL,15,Fprevent accidental poisoning.
OL,26,@tD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774026671
OL,3,CDog owners warned to keep pets away
OL,4,Cfrom daffodils, tulips and bluebells
OL,6,F"If you suspect your dog has eaten
OL,7,Fanything they shouldn't have,
OL,8,Fincluding spring bulbs, you must seek
OL,9,Fvet advice promptly, even if they are
OL,10,Fnot showing any symptoms. The sooner
OL,11,Fyour dog is treated, the better their
OL,12,Fchances of a full recovery."
OL,14,FSeveral common spring flowers and
OL,15,Fplants are poisonous to dogs. The most
OL,16,Fcommon ones include:
OL,26,@tD@\O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774026671
OL,3,CDog owners warned to keep pets away
OL,4,Cfrom daffodils, tulips and bluebells
OL,6,FDaffodils - All parts of the daffodil
OL,7,Fplant, especially the bulb, are highly
OL,8,Ftoxic to dogs. If eaten or if your dog
OL,9,Fdrinks water from a vase containing
OL,10,Fdaffodils, they can cause symptoms
OL,11,Fsuch as vomiting, diarrhoea, lethargy,
OL,12,Fand, in severe cases, seizures. Owners
OL,13,Fshould ensure that dogs cannot dig up
OL,14,For access daffodils in the garden.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774026671
OL,3,CDog owners warned to keep pets away
OL,4,Cfrom daffodils, tulips and bluebells
OL,6,FTulips - The bulbs of tulips are the
OL,7,Fmost dangerous part. If eaten, they
OL,8,Fcan irritate your dog's mouth,
OL,9,Fstomach, and skin, leading to
OL,10,Fdrooling, sickness, and even heart
OL,11,Fissues. While most cases will be
OL,12,Frelatively mild, tulip poisoning can
OL,13,Fresult in more severe symptoms,
OL,14,Fincluding difficulty breathing.
OL,16,FBluebells ` Found in woodlands and
OL,17,Fgardens, bluebells contain a toxin
OL,18,Fthat affects the heart. Ingesting
OL,19,Fbluebells can cause an upset stomach
OL,20,Fand, in large amounts, can be fatal.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774026671
OL,3,CDog owners warned to keep pets away
OL,4,Cfrom daffodils, tulips and bluebells
OL,6,FRhododendrons and Azaleas ` These
OL,7,Fvibrant plants are toxic to dogs, with
OL,8,Fall parts of the plant posing a risk.
OL,9,FEven a tiny amount can make dogs very
OL,10,Fill, and in severe cases, poisoning
OL,11,Fcan be fatal. Smaller dogs and puppies
OL,12,Fare especially vulnerable. Signs to
OL,13,Fmonitor for include excessive
OL,14,Fsalivation, vomiting, diarrhoea,
OL,15,Fdifficulty breathing, tremors, and
OL,16,Fseizures.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774026671
OL,3,CDog owners warned to keep pets away
OL,4,Cfrom daffodils, tulips and bluebells
OL,6,FAmaryllis ` Known for its striking
OL,7,Fblooms, amaryllis is also poisonous to
OL,8,Fdogs. All parts of the plant should be
OL,9,Fkept out of their reach. These plants
OL,10,Fmay irritate your dog's mouth. More
OL,11,Fsevere symptoms may include
OL,12,Fhypersalivation, vomiting, diarrhoea,
OL,13,Fmuscle weakness, tremors and worse.
OL,15,FOther spring plants that can cause
OL,16,Fproblems include Buttercups, Crocuses,
OL,17,FPrimrose, Cyclamen, Elderberry,
OL,18,FFoxglove (leaves and seeds), Hyacinth
OL,19,F(bulbs) and Lupin (leaves, seeds).
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
